title: Dean Edell Medical Show 2009.01.12
description:
This is a full episode of Dr. Dean Edell's syndicated radio program, which airs on 136 stations across the United States. This episode aired on January 12, 2009.
This episode features Dr. Edell's comments on news items including organ trafficking, a 107-year-old woman in China, cean water availability in the documentary _Flow_, a study finding a relationship between religion and self-control, and a pair of dysphagic twins who have survived into their teenage years.

He answers questions on the wisdom of hand-washing in dirty public restrooms, whether the blind have visual elements to their dreams, jetlag, carnosine for treatment of cataracts, poisonous "deathcap" mushrooms, cholesterol deposits in the eye, ginkgo biloba, and hair loss.
